  "prompt": "I temporarily deactivated my instagram, when I try to log in it says I should try again in a few hours. How long does it take to reactivate it?",
  "response": "When you temporarily deactivate your Instagram account, it typically takes a short period for the deactivation to fully process. You should generally be able to reactivate it by simply logging back in. However, if you're seeing a message advising you to try again later, it might mean that the system is still processing your request. This process can sometimes take a few hours to up to 24 hours. If you're unable to log in after waiting for a reasonable amount of time, it's a good idea to check for any service updates on Instagram's official channels or consider contacting Instagram support for assistance.",
